Pin note: v0.9.0 adds the SVG scorecard renderer. skillcard.scorecard maps a
card.json to a deterministic SVG (render_card for one skill, render_rollup for a
corpus posture), rendered headless via Textual's export_screenshot, and
`skillcard scorecard <skill-dir> --out PATH` writes it OUTSIDE the skill source —
the --out guard refuses an in-source target, since scorecard.svg is NOT in the
content_hash exclusion list and would otherwise move the skill's hash. The
v0.8.0 -> v0.9.0 diff adds skillcard/scorecard.py and touches skillcard/cli.py
plus pyproject (a new optional [scorecard] extra: textual==8.2.7, imported
lazily so validate/gate/badges stay light); hashing.py / build_card.py /
render.py / schema are unchanged, so this re-vendor moves no card content_hash.
This vendored copy is byte-identical to the v0.9.0 tag with no cabinet-local
deviation.

This is a pinned copy of Califa's `schema/` + `skillcard/` packages (including
the `skillcard.harness` subpackage, dormant here — `make check` never runs
`skillcard eval`), plus the Jinja template and pyproject, so the public
cabinet's `make check` can validate and gate skill cards without a private-repo
CI secret. v0.8.0 enabled `skillcard badges` (consumed by the badge-serving CI
job, .github/workflows/badges.yml); v0.9.0 adds `skillcard scorecard`, consumed
by `make scorecards` (scripts/build_scorecards.py) to render the per-skill and
rollup SVGs embedded in the READMEs.

Install:  python3 -m pip install -e "tooling/califa[scan,scorecard]"

